Meet <b>Marloun</b>, our citizen of the week! <br><br>This Westridge resident has been braving Millsberry's sometimes extreme weather since February 26, 2005. From his home at <a href='/home/?user=mar100'>15845 Bear Mountain View</a>, he can see the most beautiful snowy landscape. Though it's cold out right now and he has to get bundled up each day, he doesn't mind because he loves the winter scenery. <br><br>When he rides his red bicycle downtown, he usually stops by <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Tricks, Toys & Games</a> to see if there's anything new in stock. He likes to draw and has notebooks full of doodles and sketches. Classical music and oldies get him in a creative mood, and recently he finalized his plan to illustrate his own comic book series! The characters will wear a lot of red, silver, and green &mdash; his favorite colors.<br><br>Marloun is somewhat of a regular at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/arcade.phtml">Arcade</a>, and has a steadily growing trophy collection. He enjoys hanging out with his friends who live in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/main_map.phtml?location=metropark">Metro Park</a>, and is looking forward to new activities and opportunities in Millsberry this month.<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Marloun, and congratulations on being citizen of the week!<br></div>
